Overview

This project demonstrates the design and implementation of a Security Operations Center (SOC) detection and monitoring environment using Microsoft Sentinel.

The lab simulates real-world attack scenarios including privilege escalation, brute force authentication attempts, and suspicious PowerShell activity. Detection rules are built using Kusto Query Language (KQL) and mapped to MITRE ATT&CK techniques.

🏗️ Architecture
Azure Virtual Machine (Windows)
Log ingestion via Azure Monitor Agent (AMA)
Log Analytics Workspace
Microsoft Sentinel (SIEM)
🔍 Key Features
Centralized log collection from Windows VM
Custom detection rules using KQL
Incident generation and investigation workflows
MITRE ATT&CK mapping for all detections
